{"author":{"id":"cad0afbc936f740fb6048ec11d7d44bbdf0daf9970a4dbb5cf01894d5825487d"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1731563452,"nonce":"wx1ng+gVxEQgS4rzeev5A/rwUvE=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s6TjLw4","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/6166#issuecomment-2475473976"},"message":"Hi, adding a note here as we are also interested in this tool:\n\nHerro seems to be incorporated into the Dorado suite of tools (mainly used for basecalling), which was recently wrapped for Galaxy Au by @TomHarrop.  \n\nInfo about Herro in Dorado: link: https://github.com/nanoporetech/dorado (search for herro)\n\nSo it may be possible to extract this error-correction part of dorado as a standalone tool (as @TomHarrop has also done with the adapter-trimming part of dorado, to make https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/view/galaxy-australia/dorado_trimming/7ff7680fa713)\n\nA note that Herro seems to run the tool porechop first to trim nanopore adapters (https://github.com/lbcb-sci/herro), which we may not want, because this is an outdated tool and it would probably be better to use dorado's adapter-trimming tool instead. Thus it may be good to exclude the porechop part of any install if possible.","files":null}]}